aws::graph::propositions: # Helicopter Flight Training Accident Information
The accident involved an autorotation attempt followed by a tailstrike during landing.
The defining event of the accident was a tailstrike during landing-flare/touchdown.
The flight instructor was a 28-year-old female.
The flight instructor held Commercial and Flight instructor certificates.
The flight instructor had no Airplane Rating.
The flight instructor occupied the left seat.
The flight instructor had Helicopter Rating.
The flight instructor had Instrument Rating for Helicopter.
The flight instructor had Instructor Ratings for Helicopter and Instrument helicopter.
The flight instructor held a Class 2 Medical Certification without waivers/limitations.
The flight instructor's last FAA Medical Exam was on November 20, 2012.
The flight instructor was an Occupational Pilot.
The flight instructor's last Flight Review or Equivalent was on April 14, 2013.
The flight instructor had 2967 total flight hours in all aircraft.
The flight instructor had 1107 total flight hours in this make and model.
The flight instructor had 2890 Pilot In Command hours in all aircraft.
The flight instructor had 108 flight hours in the last 90 days in all aircraft.
The flight instructor had 32 flight hours in the last 30 days in all aircraft.
The student pilot was 23 years old.
The student pilot held Commercial and Flight instructor certificates.
The student pilot had Single-engine land and Multi-engine land Airplane Ratings.
The student pilot occupied the right seat.
The student pilot had Helicopter Rating.
The student pilot had Instrument Rating for Helicopter.
The student pilot had Instructor Ratings for Helicopter and Instrument helicopter.
The student pilot held a Class 2 Medical Certification without waivers/limitations.
The student pilot's last FAA Medical Exam was on March 26, 2013.
The student pilot was an Occupational Pilot.
The student pilot's last Flight Review or Equivalent was on January 3, 2013.
The student pilot had 1416 total flight hours in all aircraft.
The student pilot had 4 total flight hours in this make and model.
The student pilot had 1300 Pilot In Command hours in all aircraft.
The student pilot had 152 flight hours in the last 90 days in all aircraft.
A second pilot was present during the flight.
No toxicology was performed on either pilot.
